{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0edce42f-f48c-48b2-b151-eab011ef2f65","content":"Use **`dotnet run`**, not `dotnet test`.\n\nHot reload for tests works through the **Microsoft Testing Platform** runner, which is invoked via `dotnet run`. The flow is:\n\n```\nTESTINGPLATFORM_HOTRELOAD_ENABLED=1 dotnet run\n```\n\n`dotnet test` uses the traditional VSTest adapter and **does not** support the hot reload extension. Since your project already has `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` enabled and the `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` package, `dotnet run` will start the test host, run your tests, and then watch for file changes to re-run automatically.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"487bea85-23c4-469a-b18a-f7c927b71e3c","outputTokens":155,"requestId":"BD10:2F6EDC:1DDFD37:216A913:6A07C0B4"},"id":"30d36e62-8e3f-4eb5-b06a-5dce01685e4b","timestamp":"2026-05-16T00:56:25.840Z","parentId":"416a49b5-099d-4cbd-9e9a-3d2d2f029cec"}
